, "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Identifies declared in macros collide with identifiers passed as macro variables.\r\n\r\nI would expect that the following code macro works for with any identifier [(gist)](https://gist.github.com/8849928cdee1f15b2464b35d15b3acfc):\r\n\r\n```rust\r\ntrait X<A> {}\r\nstruct Y<A, B>(A, B);\r\nstruct Z<A, B>(A, B);\r\n\r\nmacro_rules! x {\r\n    ($S:ident, $A:ident) => (\r\n        impl<$A, B> X<B> for $S<$A, B> {}\r\n    )\r\n}\r\n\r\nx!(Y, A); // works\r\nx!(Z, B); // collides\r\n```\r\nBut it results in: \r\n```\r\nerror[E0403]: the name `B` is already used for a type parameter in this type parameter list\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/42895/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/42895/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}